deck: Sorin Markov is a Planeswalker from the plane of Innistrad.
description:
Origin

Sorin Markov was born on the plane of Innistrad. When he was imbued with the power of a vampire, the experienced caused his Planeswalker "spark" to ignite - the ability to travel freely throughout the multiverse. With this power, Sorin became a Planeswalker, and is currently one of the oldest Planeswalkers alive.

Thousands of years ago, Sorin faced off against the fearsome Eldrazi - powerful beings who fed on colored magic. Sorin, along with two other Planeswalkers, sacrificed the plane of Zendikar along with its inhabitants in order to trap the Eldrazi, preventing them from causing harm to the rest of the multiverse.

Powers and Abilities

Sorin is a powerful and experienced Planeswalker. Like all Planeswalkers, Sorin can freely travel between planes throughout the multiverse.

He is a vampire who is extremely proficient with the use of black mana.
name: Sorin Markov

deck: Grandson of Negi Springfield and a current member of the organization of immortals, UQ Holder.
description:
Current Events

With Touta's new found determination to become much stronger after seeing the large difference in strength between Fate and himself, he requests special training from Evangeline, only to be denied and granted a new mission to capture a criminal immortal. Touta and his team succeed in accomplishing the assigned mission that ended up proving to be more demanding that previously assumed and with the completion, Touta is thrown into another event (Mahora Martial Arts Tournament) with his encounter with Mana Tatsumiya, an old acquaintance of his grandfather.

Origin

Touta Kanoe is the grandson of Negi Springfield. Touta is an outspoken cheerful character and the main protagonist in the manga, UQ Holder. After his parent's death two years ago in a car accident, Touta was granted temporary immortality by his current guardian and mentor Evangeline A.K. McDowell or as Touta likes to call her, Yukihime. Due to the events two years ago, Touta has no recollection of his past. He lives his life in the countryside, with dreams of going to the Capital and climbing the "Heaven's Pillar," a space elevator located in New Tokyo. Yukihime instructed Touta that he could only leave the countryside after he defeated her in combat, and Touta tries and fails every day.

After his most recent failure to beat Yukihime, Touta and his friends get help from Tachibana, a bounty hunter disguised as a teacher. Tachibana's scheme works after Touta hands Yukihime a bracelet that restricts magic. Touta realized what was going on when Tachibana attacks his friends and Yukihime. Touta intervenes but loses his arm and gets stabbed in the heart in the process. As Touta lays on the ground grimacing in pain and blaming himself for the attack on his friends and his guardian, Yukihime interrupts him and points out to him that he's still alive even though his heart had been pierced.

Evangeline reveals to him that he had been granted temporary immortality by her two years ago which allowed him to stay alive even in his current situation. She then proceeds to give him two choices; to either let things sit as they are, and he turns to dust or lick her spilled blood from the battle with Tachibana and turn into a Vampire, gaining real immortality. Touta chooses to become a Vampire and with the sudden burst of power, he regains his lost limbs and defeats the bounty hunter. With Yukihime's Vampire identity now revealed, she and Touta now head for the Capital, New Tokyo.
name: Touta Konoe

deck: A blacksmith.
description:
Origin

A blacksmith in Whisky Jill's hometown. Smithy made Jill a lucky horseshoe that she keeps tacked to her surfboard.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

When Jill rolls back into town she a new friend named Rod McCloud with her. Smithy greets them both at his shop and sees that Rod has a chain fastened around his neck. Smithy has the bonds removed in no time.
name: Smithy

deck: Pregnant lady who is delivered by Whisky Jill.
description:
Origin

Married to John.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

Bess and John are excited for the arrival of their new baby. Whisky Jill comes to town and is just in time to deliver it. Bess does her best and delivers the baby as John waits outside. She is overjoyed to have a little girl and takes the baby outside once some commotion dies down.
name: Bess

deck: Husband of Bess in Whisky Jill's home town.
description:
Origin

Husband of Bess.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

John and Bess are excited for the arrival of their new baby. Whisky Jill comes to town and is just in time to deliver it. John waits outside and has a difficult time hearing his wife in so much pain. He is surprised when the Marshall shows up demanding Jill to come outside in the middle of the delivery. John is even more surprised when Jill comes running out with a little bundle in her arms. He is shocked when Jill throws the bundle into the air as a distraction. He is dismayed when the bundle is not caught, Jill instead running away from the Marshall. John approaches the bundle and begins to mourn his lost son. Bess shows up at the door and tells him that they actually had a girl - and she was holding her. John opens the bundle and finds his ma's vase. Relieved, he joins his wife inside.
name: John

deck: Sheriff of Saltwater.
description:
Origin

The big, burly sheriff of Saltwater. He and the towns witch, Whisky Jill, are good friends.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

When Whisky Jill rides into town the sheriff is relieved - Jill is the only person that can help deliver a baby since the trained midwife is currently drunk. Despite Jill's fears that the Marshall will catch up to her, Sheriff Hills is able to convince her to take the job. On the way to the woman in labor, however, Jill gets sidetracked into singing and dancing for the local miners in the saloon. The sheriff kindly reminds her of her chore and accompanies her to the expectant couple. Sheriff Hills takes the father, John, outside to let Jill do her work.

Outside, the sheriff does his best to comfort John despite the painful noises coming from inside. He is shocked to see the Marshall coming down the street and tries to warn Jill. He then tries to stick up for her by drawing his gun but it is shot out of his hand before it can be drawn. He then has to restrain John when Jill rushes from the house with a bundle in her arms to use as leverage against the Marshall. When all is said and done, Sheriff Hills is elated that the bundle in Jill's arms was nothing more than an old vase. He finds Jill's friend Rod McCloud and the two wait to see if Jill will come back from being chased into the mountains by the Marshall. Some townspeople want to help Jill by following but the sheriff explains that nobody comes back from Pirate Rock except for Jill, as that is Jill's home.

Jill eventually returns and the Sheriff welcomes her back heartily. He gets some supplies gathered from the townspeople and gives them to Jill and Rod as they head out on another adventure.
name: Sheriff Hills

deck: Piano player in the Saltwater saloon.
description:
Origin

Piano player in the saloon in the town of Saltwater.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

When Whisky Jill rides into town, Keyes plays a rousing rendition of "She'll Be Coming 'Round the Mountain" as Jill sings and dances around the saloon. He keeps the music going after she leaves.
name: Keyes

deck: Just a really good man.
description:
Origin

A salt miner and a citizen of Saltwater.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

Tony catches Whisky Jill after one of her rousing songs in the Saltwater saloon. He is presented to Jill's friend Rod McCloud as one of the best men in the world.
name: Tony

deck: Citizen of Saltwater.
description:
Origin

Just a lady that lives in Saltwater.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

Heather welcomes Whisky Jill and Rod McCloud to Saltwater as the pair rides in.
name: Heather

deck: Saltwater's own lookout. He has no eyes.
description:
Origin

Despite having no eyes, Lookout Pete successfully watches the road leading in to Saltwater.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

Not long after welcoming Whisky Jill home, Lookout Pete "sees" the Marshall coming into town. He slides down his tower and rushes to the saloon to alert everyone.
name: Lookout Pete

deck: A disgraced minister and town official on the hunt for Whisky Jill.
description:
Origin

The Marshall began as a preacher but hit some fairly rough times with his followers. Rumor has it that he killed a woman and her son for their constant tardiness to church; he killed two other women for dancing too provocatively; he supposedly burned his wife and son for her leaving him for another woman. The Marshall gets kicked out of the church thanks to Whisky Jill and begins to hunt her to bring her to a proper reckoning.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

The Marshall’s quest to find Whisky Jill takes him to the town of Deliverance. He enters a bar in which he is told a major scuffle took place. He sees an overcoat and demands to know how left it. The barkeep informs him of a girl with very little clothing on who cleared out his bar. The Marshall demands to know which way she went (East) and then storms out after her.

He finds her resting in a remote house. He fires a shot at her from his sniper rifle but misses. He takes aim in case she shows herself in the wrong window. Unbeknownst to the Marshall, however, is that Jill has flour dust fill the house. The Marshall is unable to tell that the person he aims at in the house is really a posse member. With another shot, the house explodes. The Marshall walks away in full confidence that he has bested Whisky Jill.

The Marshall later finds Colonel Hawkins passed out in the desert and the two men begin to travel together. They come to a camp and find three men dead. The Marshall can tell Jill has been through the area and the men move on to Saltwater, Jill's hometown. Once they get there, the Marshall tells the Colonel to stay outside the town. He then walks in alone.

The Marshall enters a bar and demands to know where Jill is. A man brashly states that only men presently occupy the bar. The Marshall grabs an ax from the wall and hacks the man's table in two. He then pulls a gun and almost shoots the man before another pipes up that Jill had left some hours before. The Marshall then takes the ax to the floor and pulls Rod out. He drags the boy down the street and puts a gun to his head to draw Jill out of a house. He threatens to shoot Rod is Jill isn't out of the house by the count of three. She exits the house and he is disappointed that seems to be using a newly born baby as a shield. He is shocked to see Jill throw the baby into the air, but snaps out of it when his pistol is whipped from his hand. He accidentally lets Rod go but decides to pursue Jill into the mountains.

In the mountains, the Marshall finds a pirate ship and walks through it. He hears steps and rushes out but finds nothing. He tries to pursue Jill through a ravine and follows her taunting words. He trips a trap and a canon fires at him, nearly hitting him. He picks up his gear and presses on. He exits the ravine at the base of a rock formation and demands Jill to show herself. He turns and sees Jill sliding down the rock formation on her surfboard. She slams into him and then tries to whip him but he is able to wrest the whip away from her before landing a punch. He stands over her victoriously and takes aim with his rifle. As he shoots, however, an arrow hits his rifle and his shot goes astray. The bullet ricochets off the mountains and hits a giant boulder that crashes down on the Marshall.

The Marshall somehow survives and continues his pursuit of Jill. He finds her camp and kidnaps Rob to trap her. It works and the Marshall overpowers her. He affixes her to her surfboard in a gulch that looks a lot like a crucifixion. He demands that Jill accept Jesus. Rain begins to fall and a huge wave floods the gulch, drowning the Marshall.
name: Marshall

description:
Origin

The father of two boys, Vincent and Billy. The three travel the West and eat people as a way of stemming the impending apocalypse.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

After consuming a family of four, Paw settles around a campfire and listens to Vincent read from the Book of Revelations about the end of the world. (The words are not quite right.) Rod McCloud enters the camp and asks about supplies. The men welcome the boy and anticipate eating him. Whiskey Jill saves Rod, however, and jabs a knife into Paw's neck. He flounders around for a second and then falls dead into the fire with his arms out. He sons die next to him. The Marshall finds their bodies some hours later and comments that the men look as if depicting the crucifixion.

Some time later, Paw is seen in a kind of afterlife listening to Vincent continue to misquote scripture.
name: Paw

deck: A "religious" man, Vincent eats people with his father and brother in the name of the Lord as a way to prevent the apocalypse.
description:
Origin

Vincent is a mighty believer in the Word of God - at least the part that he thinks says that he and his kin should eat people to appease God and stave off the apocalypse. He, his brother Billy, and his Paw travel around the West looking for people to "help" them in their worship.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

After making camp, Vincent begins reading from the Book of Revelations to his family. Billy interrupts and Vincent gets angry. The men are interrupted, however, by Rod McCloud. Vincent and the other believe Rod is there to help them prevent the apocalypse and Vincent urges his father to kill Rod. He is horrified, however, to see Whisky Jill stick a knife in his father's neck. Enraged, Vincent charges. He is also killed, but with a stick to his eye. The Marshall finds the bodies of the men a few hours later and notes that the scene somewhat resembles the crucifixion of Christ.

Some time later, Vincent is seen reading more of his misquoted scripture to Paw and Billy in some sort of afterlife.
name: Vincent

deck: Daft young cannibal who travels the West with his brother and father.
description:
Origin

A boy with a dull brain, Billy travels around eating people in the name of Christ in order to hold off the apocalypse. His favorite parts to eat are fingers.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

After having eaten a family, Billy sits around a campfire with his Paw and brother Vincent, who reads misquoted scripture. The three are surprised when a boy named Rod enters their camp. Billy practically salivates over the prospect of eating Rod's fingers. Whiskey Jill shows up and saves Rod, however, by killing each man. She snaps Billy's neck and he falls to rest beside his father.

In a sort of afterlife, Billy is seen around a campfire with his kin listening to more misquoted scripture.
name: Billy

deck: A Native American and a Hawaiian witch.
description:
Origin

Redfeather, or as she likes to be called, "Tonta," lives in a Native American village with her father and brother. She is a Hawaiian witch who carries around a surfboard in the desert.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

Redfeather is tasked by Grandmother Arrow to help their tribe relocate to higher ground. She is taken off this assignment, however, when Grandmother Arrow alerts her that a fellow Hawaiian witch friend is in trouble. Redfeather receives a bow and a single arrow and is told that she should be able to figure out when the appropriate time to use the arrow would be. She departs to find her friend, Whisky Jill.

It doesn't take long to figure out when to use the arrow. Redfeather finds Jill at the mercy of the Marshall. She fires the arrow and hits the Marshall's rifle just before he fires. This act saves Jill's life and seems to kill the Marshall when his misfired bullet ricochets into a boulder that falls on him. She leaves without saying goodbye to Jill.

Redfeather follows Jill and meets up with her in the desert. She meets Rod McCloud and helps set up camp for the night. Redfeather and Rod do some talking while Jill goes in search of firewood. Before she can react, a man hits Redfeather from behind and takes Rod. Jill rushes in with Grandmother Arrow and Redfeather tells all she can. Jill runs off and Redfeather gets cared for by her grandmother.

A bit later, Redfeather strikes out and finds Rod tied to a tree. She frees him and asks where Jill has gone. Rod explains to her that Jill said she'd be back.
name: Redfeather

deck: Resident tracker for the Hawkins Gang.
description:
Origin

A Native American employed by Colonel Hawkins to help in tracking.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

When alerted that his services were needed in tracking an escaped boy, Redskin slows down his group because he feels the atmosphere is changing - a surely bad sign. He and the group finally meets up with the Colonel. The boy has been tracked to a house and Redskin joins the other men in storming the place. Redskin finds the air thick with flour. A gun being cocked ignites the flour (due to some witchery by Whisky Jill) and the whole house explodes, killing the gang.
name: Redskin

deck: Leader of the Hawkins Gang and pursuer of Rod McCloud, a boy who can divine where water is located.
description:
Origin

Colonel Hawkins purchases Rod McCloud due to the boy's supposed abilities to locate water, even in the desert. He brands the boy with the symbol of a hawk and fish. When Rod escapes, the Colonel rounds up his men and chases after him.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

The Colonel and his posse catch up to Rod in the town of Deliverance. The boy is with a girl clad in only a bikini. The Colonel demand the boy and the girl - Whisky Jill - pulls out her whip. The Colonel grabs for his gun but is too late. The whip knocks his gun from his hand and then startles the horses. The Colonel is bucked from his horse when the gun lands on the ground and fires. As his posse rides away on the scared horses, the Colonel tries to reach his gun. Whisky Jill merely walks up to him and knocks him unconscious with her whip.

Upon waking up, the Colonel finds Jill's trail. He begins to follow it in hopes that the rest of his gang will catch up. They do and the trail leads to a solitary house. The Colonel directs his men to storm the house while he waits outside. He watches as the men burst in, but then witnesses the house blow up while Whisky Jill and Rod ride away.

The Colonel tries to walk through the desert but succumbs to his weariness and passes out in the dirt. He later wakes up and finds the Marshall standing over him. The two travel together and find a camp with three dead men. The Colonel is shocked at the dead bodies and the two men move on to Saltwater, Jill's hometown. Once they arrive, the Colonel is asked to stay outside the town. He reluctantly agrees, but only on the condition that the Marshall bring Rod back out alive and well.

Somehow the Colonel ends up with the Marshall again (the Marshall had supposedly died due to his encounter with Jill) and the two track Jill and Rod to a campsite outside of Saltwater. The Marshall catches Rod and uses him as bait to draw out Jill. Once the ploy is over, the Colonel confronts Rod and pulls off his belt to start beating the boy. Just then, a lightning strike surprises a hawk carrying a swordfish. The swordfish is dropped and it impales the Colonel, killing him instantly.
name: Colonel Hawkins

deck: A wise Native American woman and teacher of Hawaiian witches in the Old West.
description:
Origin

Little is known of Grandmother Arrow, just that she trains young Hawaiian witches and watches the skies for signs.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

Sensing something great is at hand, Grandmother Arrow tasks her grandson, Running Hare, to be on the watch for a hawk carrying a fish across the desert. After some time Running Hare reports to her that he has seen the sign. She orders him to bring his sister Redfeather. He leaves and she begins a ceremony.

Redfeather arrives and Grandmother Arrow asks her granddaughter to stop moving the tribe to higher ground and to go help her friend Whisky Jill. She gives Redfeather a bow and a single arrow and challenges her to know the right time to use it. Redfeather departs.

After Redfeather leaves, Grandmother Arrow performs a meditation ritual. She senses a change in the air and departs. She finds Jill and the two exchange barbs. Grandmother Arrow is impressed that Jill has found Rod, the Great Diviner. She warns her that something bad is going to happen. The two women hear a scuffle and find Redfeather injured and Rod missing. Grandmother Arrow informs Jill that this will be her last test to becoming a true Hawaiian witch. She stays with Redfeather while Jill goes to find Rod.
name: Grandmother Arrow

deck: A watcher for the sign of a hawk carrying a fish in the desert.
description:
Origin

A Native American living in the West in the 1800s. His sister is the Hawaiian witch Redfeather.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

Grandmother Arrow gives Running Hare the task of watching the skies for a hawk carrying a fish. After some time, Running Hare sees the sign. He runs to report to Grandmother Arrow and asks her how a hawk could catch a fish in the middle of the desert. He is assured that all is well and is tasked with fetching his sister.
name: Running Hare

deck: Right hand man in the Hawkins Gang.
description:
Origin

One of Colonel Hawkins's men.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

When Rod McCloud escapes from Colonel Hawkins, Lloyd is called upon to help track the young boy. They find him in the town of Deliverance but Lloyd and a few of the other men are chased off by Whisky Jill’s whip. Lloyd meets back up with the Colonel while more men are brought into the hunt. The two track Whisky Jill and Rod to a solitary house in the middle of nowhere. Lloyd charges the house with the rest of the gang but finds it empty. The air, however, is filled with flour dust. This ignites when a gun is cocked (due to Whisky Jill's magic) and the house is blown to bits, killing Lloyd and the rest of his crew.
name: Lloyd

deck: A young boy that can divine the location of water.
description:
Origin

Unable to explain why, Rod has the ability to find water. He is also haunted by dreams of a minister condemning someone during a lightning storm.

Creation

Written and drawn by Fresherluke.

Major Story Arcs

After being purchased by Colonel Hawkins, Rod is able to find a way to escape. He does so and flees across the desert to a town called Deliverance. He collapses in the arms of a girl as Colonel Hawkins catches up. While his is asleep, the girl (whom he will learn is Whisky Jill) defeats the Colonel and takes Rod out of town. He wakes up at a watering hole and officially meets Jill. The two ride together and find a house to rest in. The Hawkins Gang catches up and Rod and Jill have to sneak out. (Jill makes the house explode somehow by having Rod blow flour dust everywhere.)

Out in the desert, the two realize that they left all their gear at the house. Jill is panicked and thinks they will die. Rod divines the location of water and digs a hole. He is surprised that this show of his powers doesn't make Jill angry. He is relieved when she shows a genuine interest in his abilities.

Rod and Jill find a camp that night and see three people around a fire. Rod is convinced to approach the men and ask for supplies. He does so and lies that he is alone in the desert. The men ask Rod to join them as they read from the Bible and he reluctantly sits in the middle of them all. It is soon apparent that they are crazy and intend to eat him. He is saved, however, by Jill popping out from the shadows and killing the three men. The two move on after claiming all their supplies.

Once in Saltwater, Rod is introduced to the sheriff and salt miners of the town. He is left in their company as Jill heads off to deliver a baby. The men are alerted, however, to the Marshall's arrival and the men hide Rod under the floorboards of the saloon. He peaks through the cracks and sees the Marshall. The Marshall is somehow tipped off as to Rod's whereabouts and Rod barely manages to dodge an ax taken to the floor before he is ripped out by the Marshall and asked to accept Jesus before he dies. Rod is then dragged down the street to a house where Jill is delivering a baby. The Marshall puts a gun to Rod's head to draw Jill out. When Jill appears, she asks Rod what she should do. Rod tells her to beat the Marshall down. He watches as Jill seems to throw a baby into the air and then whip the Marshall's pistol from his hand. The Marshall lets Rod go and the boy runs to the safety of the townspeople. He watches Jill run to some nearby mountains with her surfboard with the Marshall in hot pursuit. He wants to go help Jill, but Sheriff Hills explains that nobody comes out of Pirate Rock except Jill, as that is her home.

Rod waits in town, despite the sounds of gunfire and rockslides. He is elated when Jill comes back down the mountain. She takes him to meet Smithy, a blacksmith who takes the iron clasp from Rod's neck. Once freed, Rod and Jill head out to find other adventures. Their first night camping, Jill takes off Rod's shirt to inspect a branding she had seen in town. He is uncomfortable, as he assumes Jill is coming on to him. He explains that he got branded by Colonel Hawkin. He gets a little creeped out when Jill kisses the brand. He gets even more creeped out when she begins spooning him on his mat. She asks about his dreams and he tells her they he thought they once dealt with a future event, but it must not be the case anymore. Rod is wrong, however, and his nightmares about the Marshall crucifying Jill returns - despite hearing that the Marshall is dead.

The next day, Rod is shocked to hear that Jill is intent on marrying him. The conversation is cut short when Rod sees Redfeather off in the distance. The three make camp and Jill leaves to get firewood. Rod tries to get Redfeather to talk but they are interrupted when the Marshall hits Redfeather over the head and takes Rod. Rod is tied up and left at the foot of a tree as a trap for Jill. The Colonel shows up after Jill has been captured and tries to exact revenge on Rod by beating him with a belt. Before he can, however, Rod is saved by a swordfish that falls from the sky - dropped by a hawk.

With no one to untie him, Rod falls asleep. In the morning he sees Jill standing over him. She is wet from a wave she was able to ride the previous night in the storm. Rod sees that she is going to leave him and he asks for a kiss. She kisses him and tells him she'll be back. Rod watches her leave.
name: Rod McCloud
